This paper deals with the problem of sarcasm detection in text, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The paper uses machine learning algorithms to classify text as sarcastic or not, which falls under the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of latent semantic spaces, which is a technique commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL, cs.AI, and cs.LG, followed by cs.IR and cs.CY.
